Reasoning: The paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach is based on deep learning (cs.AI) and involves aligning feature distributions (cs.CL). Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset (DomainNet) for benchmarking multi-source domain adaptation methods, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
